# Append-only hardware/cost ledger. One line per (rev, Modal app). Each entry
# references an alpha-rev via `refs.{hypothesis_id, rev}`; multiple entries
# per rev are expected (build, probe, retries, failed attempts).
#
# This file is DECOUPLED from research/hypotheses.jsonl: the absence of a
# ledger entry NEVER blocks an alpha-rev. Hardware/cost info can be backfilled.
#
# `billing.actual_cost_usd` is pulled from `modal billing report --json`, NOT
# estimated. `pulled_at` records when. If a billing window has not yet closed
# (e.g. the same calendar day), the cost figure may move; pull again later
# and append a corrective entry rather than editing.
#
# Schema (subject-to-evolve, append-only):
#   ts                       ISO-8601 UTC timestamp the entry was written
#   refs.hypothesis_id       e.g. "HD1"
#   refs.rev                 the rev this hardware was used for
#   modal_app_id             unique ap-* id (one Modal app = one entry)
#   workspace                Modal workspace (e.g. "ksagachev")
#   stage                    free-form short tag: "build" | "probe" | "smoke" | ...
#   hw.class                 "modal_cpu" | "modal_gpu" | "gcp_vm" | ...
#   hw.vcpu, hw.memory_gib, hw.gpu, hw.parallel_containers
#   timing.wall_s            outer wall-clock (incl. image build, scheduling)
#   timing.function_elapsed_s  inner @app.function execution (build) or
#                              gpu_seconds_total (probe; sum over parallel
#                              containers), whichever is meaningful
#   per_unit_gpu_s           [optional] per-container/seed timings
#   billing.actual_cost_usd  realized cost, from `modal billing report --json`
#   billing.source           CLI command used
#   billing.pulled_at        when the billing query was made
#   note                     [optional] free text (failures, retries, etc.)
